Author:  BARKER
Vol / Page:  186
Edition:  1874
Quote:  I saw the bushmen whispering together, and examining(?) the rocks in some places, ... One of them had been a digger, and was pronouncing an opinion that this creek was very likely to prove a `home of gold' some day. ... At this time of the year the water is very shallow, ...; and  they talk of having `found the colour' (of gold) in some places.
